The evidence with the title 'Key facts about the uninsured population | the Henry J. Kaiser ... ' says Sep 19, 2017  ... Data show substantial gains in public and private insurance coverage and historic decreases in uninsured rates under the ACA . Coverage gains were particularly large among low - income people living in states that expanded Medicaid. Still, millions of people—27.6 million in 2016 — remain uninsured. 
